09/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Customs officials seized 20kg of heroin Sunday (August 8th) at the Gradina border crossing point with Bulgaria. 
Interior Minister Ivica Dacic described it as the biggest drug seizure in Serbia this year. 
The street value is estimated at 500,000 euros. 
The heroin was allegedly found in a car driven by two Dutch citizens of Turkish origin, who were travelling from Turkey to The Netherlands. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 09/08/10)
